The paper discusses model-driven engineering, which is a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE). The focus is on model comparison and differencing, which involves algorithms for matching and identifying differences between models. This relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and databases (cs.DB) as models are often represented using formal languages and stored in databases. The paper also discusses the limitations of current algorithms and proposes solutions, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques.
